vant today. This study also explores the relationship between melodrama as a genre of manichean worldviews and law as a system of binary oppositions and discusses de Burgos's subversion of the former as a means to criticise the latter. Anja Louis is a lecturer in the Department of Spanish at the University of Sheffield.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aLaw in literature. 4aHispanic Studies. 4aWomen's & Gender Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aAnglo-American legal theory.  aCarmen de Burgos.  aLaw in literature.  aLaw.  aLegal critique.  aPolitical propaganda.  aSpanish history.  aSpanish literature.  aSpanish writer.  aTwentieth-century literature.  aWomen's literature.  aWomen's studies.  afeminism.  agender.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846154379423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846154379/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles